          <msContents>
            <summary>An account, in verse, of the birth and life of the prophet
                                <persName key="n 79062738" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/66440309/">Zoroaster</persName>, by Zartusht Bahram Pazhdu, the author of
                                <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Ard&#x101;v&#x12B;r&#x101;fn&#x101;mah</title> in verse and
                                <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="alt"> D&#x101;st&#x101;n-i Jingihir
                                Nigh&#x101;jah</title> (Persian MS 301). The title is given in the
                            Manuscript on folio <locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus> as <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Mawl&#x16B;d-i Zartusht</title><title xml:lang="per">&#x645;&#x648;&#x644;&#x648;&#x62F; &#x632;&#x631;&#x62A;&#x634;&#x62A;</title> The same is also given in the
                            text on folio<locus from="61v" to="61v">61v</locus>&#x686;&#x648; &#x645;&#x648;&#x644;&#x648;&#x62F; &#x632;&#x631;&#x62A;&#x634;&#x62A; &#x62E;&#x648;&#x627;&#x646;&#x6CC;
                            &#x62A;&#x645;&#x627;&#x645; / &#x628;&#x62F;&#x644; &#x6A9;&#x646; &#x628;&#x631;&#x648; &#x622;&#x641;&#x631;&#x6CC;&#x646;&#x6CC; &#x62A;&#x645;&#x627;&#x645; . The same title is also given in the
                            author&#x2019;s other work, <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Jingihir
                                Nigh&#x101;jah</title><title xml:lang="per">&#x62C;&#x646;&#x6AF;&#x647;&#x631; &#x646;&#x6AF;&#x647;&#x627;&#x686;&#x647;</title> (Persian
                            301), where he states that his mother used to read to him two works
                            (daftar), the Mawl&#x16B;d-i Zartusht and the Ard&#x101;-y&#x12B; v&#x12B;r&#x101;f &#x62F;&#x648; &#x62F;&#x641;&#x62A;&#x631; &#x628;&#x648;&#x62F; &#x646;&#x642;&#x644;
                            &#x627;&#x646;&#x62F;&#x631; &#x628;&#x631; &#x645;&#x646; &#x6A9;&#x62A;&#x627;&#x628;&#x6CC; &#x628;&#x648;&#x62F; &#x632;&#x627;&#x646; &#x645;&#x648;&#x644;&#x648;&#x62F; &#x632;&#x631;&#x62A;&#x634;&#x62A; &#x62F;&#x631;&#x648; &#x686;&#x6CC;&#x632;&#x6CC; &#x6A9;&#x647; &#x628;&#x62F; &#x645;&#x642;&#x635;&#x648;&#x62F; &#x632;&#x631;&#x62A;&#x634;&#x62A;. The
                            beginning of this Manuscript corresponds with that in Sachau/Ethe
                            (British Library) and to some extent to that in Rieu (British Museum),
                            but is different from that in Ethe (10): </summary>
